mention.text: Argument The Genius of the place
Stay your rude steps ; whose throbbing breasts infold The legion-fiends of Glory , or of Gold !
thee my borders nurse the fragrant wreath
purer day ; Whose finer sense each soft vibration owns With sweet responsive sympathy of tones
my borders nurse the fragrant wreath
their trackless way ; My plumy pairs , in gay embroidery dress
-- Hither , emerging from yon orient skies , Botanic Goddess !
her Zephyrs with the shafts of Love , Pleased Gnomes , ascending from their earthy beds
orient beams ; Musk 'd in the rose 's lap fresh dews
Fringing Night 's sable robe with transient beams
Ride , with broad eye and scintillating hair
The rapid fire-ball through the midnight air
Alarm with comet-blaze the sapphire plain

her still centre tread the burning soil , And watch the billowy lavas , as they boil ; Where , in basaltic caves imprisoned deep , Reluctant fires in dread suspension sleep ; Or sphere on sphere in widening waves expand
the mother-bird on moss-wove nest Lulls her fond brood beneath her plumy breast ; Warmth from her tender heart
You from deep cauldrons and unmeasured caves
vitrescent waves ; O'er shining oceans ray volcanic light
the sacred sun in Memnon 's fane
Guard from cold dews her love-illumined form
the surge with insect-sparks , that swarm Round the bright oar
the savage from his native wood
Slumbers in grim repose the sooty mass
Pent in dark chambers of cylindric brass
